properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 17 at 3:18AM PST until January 18 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible above 2000 feet. Total snow
accumulations of 8 to 12 inches at the passes. Higher
elevations above 3000 feet could see accumulations 12-24
inches. Winds could gust as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area, Cascade
mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King Counties,
including Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade
mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis Counties, including
the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From this evening through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON ABOVE 2000 FEET
